edu.ucla.sspace.matrix

Enum MatrixIO.Format

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MatrixIO.Format>
      • edu.ucla.sspace.matrix.MatrixIO.Format
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<MatrixIO.Format>
    Enclosing class:
    MatrixIO

    public static enum MatrixIO.Format
extends Enum<MatrixIO.Format>
    An enum that specifies the formatting used for the matrix that is serialized in a file. Format specifications are as follows:
    format
    description
    DENSE_TEXT Each row is on its own line, with each column being delimited by one or more white space characters. All rows should have the same number of columns.
    MATLAB_SPARSE The sparse format supported by Matlab. See here for full details.
    SVDLIBC_SPARSE_TEXT The sparse human readable format supported by SVDLIBC. See here for full details.
    SVDLIBC_DENSE_TEXT The dense human readable format supported by SVDLIBC. See here for full details.
    SVDLIBC_SPARSE_BINARY The sparse binary format supported by SVDLIBC. See here for full details.
    SVDLIBC_DENSE_BINARY The dense binary format supported by SVDLIBC. See here for full details.
